A 'Tringa semipalmata' is a species of small wading bird, also known as the 'Willet'.
It has brownish-gray upperparts, a white belly, and a distinctive black and white striped wing pattern.
On the head, it has a long, slender bill that is slightly curved downwards.
It also has semi-webbed feet, which are visible when it is wading in shallow water.
The 'Tringa semipalmata' is commonly found in coastal areas throughout North and South America.
It feeds on a variety of invertebrates, including crustaceans and worms.
Due to its unique appearance and habitat, the 'Tringa semipalmata' is a popular subject for wildlife photographers and birdwatchers.
